body_html:
So now the error is different. Earlier the error was "tensorflow-1.0.0rc0" is not a supported. Unfortunately I cannot help you with tensorflow_fold issues. I suggest you file an issue here.

My unofficial advice would be to try this:

wget https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow_fold/tensorflow_fold-0.0.1-cp27-none-linux_x86_64.whl
mv tensorflow_fold-0.0.1-cp27-none-linux_x86_64.whl tensorflow_fold-0.0.1-cp27-cp27mu-manylinux1_x86_64.whl 
pip install tensorflow_fold-0.0.1-cp27-cp27mu-manylinux1_x86_64.whl

My theory is that your virtualenv does not like the whl file extension.

body:
So now the error is different. Earlier the error was "tensorflow-1.0.0rc0" is not a supported. Unfortunately I cannot help you with tensorflow_fold issues. I suggest you file an issue [here](https://github.com/tensorflow/fold/issues). 

My unofficial advice would be to try this:
```
wget https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow_fold/tensorflow_fold-0.0.1-cp27-none-linux_x86_64.whl
mv tensorflow_fold-0.0.1-cp27-none-linux_x86_64.whl tensorflow_fold-0.0.1-cp27-cp27mu-manylinux1_x86_64.whl 
pip install tensorflow_fold-0.0.1-cp27-cp27mu-manylinux1_x86_64.whl 
``` 

My theory is that your virtualenv does not like the whl file extension.
